The GEO Group, Inc. is a correctional facility management firm with facilities located in the US, UK, Australia, and South Africa. Founded in 1984 as the Wackehnhut Corrections corporation, it now operates more than 60 facilities across the US, Australia,… MoreThe GEO Group, Inc. is a correctional facility management firm with facilities located in the US, UK, Australia, and South Africa. Founded in 1984 as the Wackehnhut Corrections corporation, it now operates more than 60 facilities across the US, Australia, the United Kingdom, and South Africa. 

On April 6, 2017, The Geo Group acquired Community Education Centers (CEC). Community Education Centers, Inc. was a provider of recovery, treatment and and education services for adult correctional populations in the United States, with approximately 97 facilities across 22 states. It was founded in 1996 and was privately held.
IT Priorities:
•The IT department at GEO Group Inc. is primarily focused on providing consistent network and voice services to its prison facilities, and maintaining business management and physical security systems.
•The company has placed a strong emphasis on technical training for… MoreIT Priorities:
•The IT department at GEO Group Inc. is primarily focused on providing consistent network and voice services to its prison facilities, and maintaining business management and physical security systems.
•The company has placed a strong emphasis on technical training for its staff.

IT Structure:
•IT for the GEO Group Inc. is directed from the company headquarters in Boca Raton, FL but also has offices to support different facilities in the Eastern, Central, and Western regional offices.
•A field technology team is responsible for maintaining the facilities systems for the company nationwide, and provides support to the company's regional offices.

IT Intelligence Snippets:
•The company primarily utilizes Symantec and IBM systems for its storage and security solutions, and Infinium for its ERP needs.  BlackBerry Enterprise Server handles the company's mobile devices.
•GEO Group maintains a large number of subsidiary companies, including Abraxas System for Adolescent Females, Just Care, Inc., BI Inc., Correctional Service Corp., Cornell Companies, and GEO Transportation.





